Cell C has appointed Tyrone Soondarjee as its new chief financial officer, effective from 1 July 2017. Soondarjee was the financial director at the Sasfin Group, a position he held since 2010. Previously, he held several executive positions at the Deloitte & Touche Group, and was the FD at TNBS Mutual Bank. He is a chartered accountant and received his BCompt Honours degree from Unisa. Soondarjee will take over from Robert Pasley, who will return to his original role as chief strategy officer, said Cell C.